Feature: [Automation] JIRA - GitHub Linkage
  # Jira Ticket : QA-1321
  # Description : Issue: Currently, when users schedule creatives, they might unintentionally leave part of a line item flight with no active creatives. This results in periods where no creative will run — in most cases, this is an unwanted consequence or mistake from the user’s perspective and can lead to missed delivery. Description: Only check for scheduling gaps if all creatives in the tactic have a schedule applied. When all creatives are scheduled: Combine the scheduled dates of all creatives. Compare this combined coverage against all line item flights. If there is any date inside a flight where no creatives are active, show a single warning above the creative table. If at least one creative is unscheduled, assume full coverage for all flights and do not show a warning. The warning applies to the tactic as a whole, not to individual creatives. Logic: Check for unscheduled creatives: If  any  creative in the tactic has  no schedule applied , treat it as running for the full duration of all LI flights. In this case, there can be  no scheduling gaps  and  no warning  should be displayed. If all creatives have schedules: For each LI flight, take the  start date  and  end date . Merge all creative date ranges into a single  coverage timeline . Identify uncovered date ranges  inside each LI flight  where no creative is active. Gap detection rules: Only detect gaps within LI flights. Ignore uncovered dates outside all LI flights. Dates are inclusive for both start and end. Use the Line Item’s time zone. Display warning if gaps exist: Count all gaps across all LI flights → display in banner: Warning: X gap(s) in flight coverage. Show a single tooltip listing  all gaps  in chronological order: No creatives will serve between [MMM D] and [MMM D, YYYY]; [MMM D] and [MMM D, YYYY]; … and [MMM D] and [MMM D, YYYY], due to scheduling gaps.   QA Examples: Example A — 1 gap across all flights    Line Item flights: Jan 1–Jan 31, 2025 Feb 1–Feb 28, 2025 Apr 1–Apr 30, 2025 Creatives: Creative A — Jan 1, 2025 → Feb 9, 2025 Creative B — Feb 15, 2025 → Apr 30, 2025 Creative C — Jan 1, 2025 → Jan 31, 2025 Creative D — Jan 1, 2025 → Apr 30, 2025 Creative E —Jan 1, 2025 → Apr 30, 2025 Detected gap: Feb 10–Feb 14, 2025 Expected UI: Banner:  Warning: 1 gap(s) in flight coverage. Tooltip:  No creatives will serve between Feb 10 and Feb 14, 2025, due to scheduling gaps. Example B — 4 gaps across all flights    Line Item flights: Jan 1–Jan 31, 2025 Feb 1–Feb 28, 2025 Mar 1–Mar 31, 2025 Apr 1–Apr 30, 2025 Creatives: Creative A — Jan 1, 2025 → Jan 10, 2025 Creative B — Jan 13, 2025 → Feb 9, 2025 Creative C — Feb 15, 2025 → Mar 19, 2025 Creative D — Mar 26, 2025 → Apr 4, 2025 Creative E — Apr 11, 2025 → Apr 30, 2025 Detected gaps: Jan 11–Jan 12, 2025 Feb 10–Feb 14, 2025 Mar 20–Mar 25, 2025 Apr 5–Apr 10, 2025 Expected UI: Banner:  Warning: 4 gap(s) in flight coverage. Tooltip:  No creatives will serve between Jan 11 and Jan 12, 2025; Feb 10 and Feb 14, 2025; Mar 20 and Mar 25, 2025; and Apr 5 and Apr 10, 2025, due to scheduling gaps. Release Prep(Development/QA) None UX Source File Example A — 1 gap across all flights    Example B — 4 gaps across all flights    UX Prototype  

